commText: Prithvi Shaw and Warner are at the crease. Prithvi Shaw is on strike. Gerald Coetzee will open the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short of length and rising at Prithvi Shaw's throat, he fends uncomfortably and luckily it doesn't go straight up
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, SIX, no third man and it's six. A short of length delivery outside off, Prithvi Shaw flashes the cut and it flies all the way
A wide slip.
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, no run, full outside off, pushed off the front foot to cover-point
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short of length on the stumps, tucked to mid-wicket
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, no run, full on the stumps, clipped to mid-on

Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, direct-hit from David and Prithvi Shaw was struggling I guess. He ran in a wide line and that might have cost him, driven to mid-on and Shaw set off, replays show that Shaw was well short
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short of length outside off, dabbed to short third man
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, back of a length and swerving back in from outside off, Prithvi Shaw drives to cover-point and does not beat the fielder
A wide slip.
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, wide yorker length delivery outside off, Prithvi Shaw tries to glide it down with an open face, can only squirt it behind him off a thick inside-edge
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, slides it down leg, Prithvi Shaw swings it away to fine-leg, poor delivery and a rare one from Bumrah
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, good short ball, dug in as Prithvi Shaw makes room outside the leg-stump, left alone and it's a fair delivery
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length outside off, dabbed to short third man
Akash Madhwal, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Akash Madhwal to Warner, no run, full outside off, Warner drives and it's a thick inside-edge on to the back leg, almost dragged back on
Akash Madhwal to Warner, no run, short of length outside off, skiddy and low, Warner cuts and misses
Akash Madhwal to Warner, no run, full and right up there on off, driven to mid-off
Akash Madhwal to Warner, no run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length on the stumps, Warner shuffles across to play the lap, misses, hit on the thigh and sliding down leg
Akash Madhwal to Warner, FOUR, full on the stumps, sliding into the pads, flicked over mid-wicket and runs away, Warner is away
Akash Madhwal to Warner, no run, back of a length just outside off, Warner mistimes the pull to mid-wicket
Romario Shepherd, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short of length just outside off, defended to backward point
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, back of a length and angling into off-stump, Prithvi Shaw drags the pull to deep sq
Shepherd to Warner, SIX, massive hit. A good length delivery on middle-stump, Warner sinks low and heaves it into the top tier at deep backward square leg, that's his go-to shot
Shepherd to Warner, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shepherd to Warner, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Shepherd comes back with a wicket. Wide slower ball full outside off, Warner sinks low to loft, off the toe-end and a dolly to mid-on. That is such a big wicket. Shepherd after the heroics with the bat, now has a wicket. Warner c Hardik Pandya b Shepherd 10(8) [4s-1 6s-1]
Abishek Porel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Shepherd to Abishek Porel, 1 run, good length and angling into the pads, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full on off, driven to mid-on who is deep
Akash Madhwal to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short of length on off, pulled straight to the fielder at mid-wicket
Akash Madhwal to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, dug in short outside off, Prithvi Shaw does well to reach and ramp that over Kishan, one hand came off the bat as he played that
Akash Madhwal to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, no deep mid-wicket and four. A skiddy short of length delivery on off, short-arm jabbed wide of mid-wicket
Akash Madhwal to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, short of length on the middle and leg line, pulled straight to the fielder at deep square leg
Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, no run, full outside off, Abishek Porel gets forward to drive to mid-off

Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, no run, pitching outside the leg-stump, full on the pads, Abishek Porel flicks and misses, is rapped on the pads and is in pain, down he goes, might need medical attention

Summary 1-5 overs: - Shaw slashes and gets a six - Bumrah keeps Shaw quiet - Madhwal begins with a tight over - Warner smacks Shepherd for a six but the bowler gets him next ball - Shaw manages to his successive fours off Madhwal
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, short of length on off, Prithvi Shaw pulls and clears mid-on, just about enough bat
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, no run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length on the stumps, Prithvi Shaw makes room to push to mid-off
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, wide, short at Prithvi Shaw who bends and then tries the ramp, does not connect. DC have reviewed this, it's a wide
Shepherd to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, slugged to deep mid-wicket
Shepherd to Abishek Porel, no run, full outside off, from round the wicket, Abishek Porel drives and misses
Shepherd to Abishek Porel, FOUR, deft touch. A short of length delivery just outside off, Abishek Porel opens the face of the bat and runs it wide of short third man who did not dive

Shepherd to Abishek Porel, 3 runs, slower ball full outside off, Abishek Porel gets forward to drive wide of the diving cover-point, David gives chase and pulls it back, just in the nick of time, saves one run
Mohammad Nabi, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Lowest PP total for DC this IPL
Nabi to Abishek Porel, 1 run, to long-on, Abishek flicks to long-on
No slip as of now
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, quick and into the wicket, Shaw flicks through mid-wicket
Nabi to Abishek Porel, 1 run, full and on the stumps, Abishek flicks along the ground to long-on
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, leg-side flat ball, clipped to long-on
Nabi to Abishek Porel, 1 run, quicker delivery, Abishek punches it through mid-on
Nabi is bowling over the RHB and round the wicket to LHB
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, 2 runs, mistimed pull to the right of deep mid-wicket as Nabi bowls short into the wicket
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Abishek Porel, no run, googly just outside off stump, Abishek mistimes the punch back to the bowler
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, flicks leg-side to deep mid-wicket
Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, SIX, finally they tee off! Leggie in the slot as the tease, but Shaw is set and executes the slog-sweep handsomely over long-on. Cleared his front leg out early and smacked it
Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, now anticipates the bowler to go short and goes deep in the crease for a cut shot past backward point. Third man is up and it's four easily
Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, now it's full and in the slot and Shaw thumps it down the ground for four more. This is the over DC badly wanted to inject life into this game
Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, oh leading edge flies towards long-off as he closes the bat face early

That 16-run over has forced the timeout one over early for MI. Still the home team is miles ahead and the pitch doesn't seem to be easing for batting. DC need a couple of really big overs to bring that asking rate down
Gerald Coetzee [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, length and width outside off stump, Shaw cuts to deep cover
Gerald Coetzee to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower delivery outside off stump, Abishek cuts square of the wicket on the off-side

Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, lovely placement and this is a good fifty for Shaw. Wasn't at his fluent best but played the situation and hung in there. Short delivery on the stumps, Shaw rolls his wrists on the pull to keep it along the round through backward square leg

Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, that's four more! Really poor short delivery wide of off stump, Prithvi reaches out and cuts over backward point, big open space there to the left of deep point and it's four
Gerald Coetzee to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, good length delivery outside off stump, Shaw punches square of the wicket on the off-side
Gerald Coetzee to Abishek Porel, FOUR, more dishing out poor stuff from Gerald Coetzee. Tried the yorker but offered a slot delivery and Abishek Porel thumps it down the ground
First 50+ score for Prithvi Shaw against MI in 12 IPL innings
31 runs off the last 2 overs. Hardik is desperate for a breakthrough. Does he turn to Bumrah now?
Mohammad Nabi [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, low full toss, Shaw drives to deep cover
Nabi to Abishek Porel, 1 run, flatter delivery on the off stump, Porel works it to deep mid-wicket
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, really full delivery on the stumps, Shaw slog-sweeps to deep backward square leg
Nabi to Abishek Porel, 1 run, shortish delivery, Porel works it through backward square leg
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, no run, full delivery, driven straight to cover
Nabi to Prithvi Shaw, SIX, in the airrrr and just over deep backward square leg who ran to the left and jumped to get a hand on it

Over Summary (6-10 ov) * Shephard concedes 13 runs in the 6th over of the innings * Piyush Chawla concedes 16 runs in the 8th over - Shaw hit him for a six and 2 fours * Prithvi Shaw completes a 31-ball half-century * DC reach 94 for 1 at the halfway stage of the innings
Akash Madhwal [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, FOUR, in the airrr, doesn't carry to long-on oh Nabi fumbles and allows the ball to go for four. Didn't get the body behind the line as he had to tackle awkward bounce. Was a full delivery, Abishek hit the drive over mid-on and got away
Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, oh nicely guided away past backward point and they get two more
Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, 1 run, now the full wide yorker, Abishek squeezes it off the front foot to backward point
Akash Madhwal to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, lovely slower delivery on the stumps, Shaw mistimes the drive to long-on

Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, FOUR, finally Abishek manages to slice past point for four. The first try was cut off in the deep, second was stopped in the circle. Now stays leg-side and slices this length delivery and third man was up

Akash Madhwal to Abishek Porel, 1 run, oh dropped. Fairly easy catch at this level. Full toss, Abishek tried to swing to leg-side, leading edge flies to the right of extra-cover. Coetzee moved to his right and dived but spilled the catch. Looks even more simpler on the replay
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower delivery on the stumps, Abishek defends to mid-on. Prithvi Shaw bumps into Bumrah as he takes the run, loses the bat in the process
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, very full delivery on the leg stump, Prithvi flicks to deep mid-wicket
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, yorker on the stumps, Abishek digs it out
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 1 run, dipping slower ball yorker, Abishek digs it out to mid-off
Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, out Bowled!! There's the cunning toe-crusher that forces the batter into hiding his back leg. Bumrah the man for the breakthrough again. Brilliant yorker angling in, Prithvi Shaw was already smart enought to stay leg-side to avoid injury, but this was heading right to that back foot and he had to move it out. Couldn't get his bat down in time and the leg stump lies flat on the ground. End of a decent innings from Shaw. Prithvi Shaw b Bumrah 66(40) [4s-8 6s-3]
Prithvi Shaw vs Bumrah in IPL 22 balls 16 runs two dismissals Avg: 8.0 SR: 72.72
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, slower delivery, Stubbs dabs to short third man
Interesting that DC still look for a left-right combo and send Stubbs over Pant with the asking rate too high
Piyush Chawla [1.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Chawla to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, smashed that drive to extra-cover, fielder slows it down and they get two

Chawla to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, in the airrr, Tilak dives at deep mid-wicket and it's just over him. Stubbs picked this googly and slog-swept this high, didn't middle it but the boundaries aren't big here and he gets a maximum
Chawla to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, nudged to mid-wicket
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, outside off stump, Abishek slices this to short third man, Bumrah goes to the bowler's end for the direct-hit but is off target
Chawla to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, another slot ball and this time Stubbs nails the slog-sweep so high over mid-wicket. Lovely sound and height on that hit
Chawla to Tristan Stubbs, no run, off-side ball, driven straight to deep cover. 16 off the the first over from Chawla, 16 off the second too al
Stubbs will look to target Romario
Romario Shepherd [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Shepherd to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower delivery, Abishek cuts well, but Tilak dives full length to the left at backward point and saves three
Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, full delivery outside off stump, Stubbs leans forward and drives to deep cover
Pant and Ponting hinting at a timeout to the 4th ump
Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, yorker on the stumps, Stubbs dig it out to mid-on
Boucher and Malinga giving inputs to Hardik at the boundary
Shepherd to Abishek Porel, 1 run, nice slower full delivery, Abishek drives to long-off

Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, and there's the one loose ball almost inevitable every over. Romario tried the yorker but Stubbs played a brilliant straight drive as he was able to get under that overpitched ball
Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, slow into the wicket, pulled wide of long-on and they race back for two

Timeout. Six overs 97 to get. Stubbs looking brilliant, Pant to come, but MI have two overs of Bumrah. Even if they manage 20 off him, they got to somehow get the rest against the rest. This is a real toughie for DC
At the end of the 14th over: \nMI - 131/4 \nDC - 138/2
Hardik wants to get Stubbs ASAP so he's given the third to Bumrah early than usual
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, oh beaten!
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 1 run, full delivery on the stumps, Abishek drills it to long-on
Bumrah to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, the killer yorker, Stubbs digs it out to the leg-side

Bumrah to Abishek Porel, FOUR, smart! Knows Bumrah is going for the poles, so he moves across early for the scoop. Pace off meant Abishek had the time to adjust his bat swing and he glances it past short fine leg
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, the fast off-side yorker just outside off stump, Abishek tries to squeeze it out but misses
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Tim David!! Full toss and it's got him a wicket. Tried the yorker and missed by a big margin. Good thing was he cramped the batter for room so Abishek lost shape on the slog, sliced it high towards long-on and Tim David ain't dropping those. Just six and a wicket in that over Abishek Porel c Tim David b Bumrah 41(31) [4s-5]

Over Summary (11-15 ov) * Porel dropped by Coetzee off Madhwal on 30 * Bumraj bowls a perfect leg-stump yorker to uproot Shaw for 66 * Stubbs gets going with a couple of massive sixes off Piyush Chawla * Shephard concedes 11 runs in the 14th over * Two excellent overs from Bumrah keeps the pressure on Delhi Capitals * Porel holes out to long-on off Bumrah for 41
Fewest matches to 150 IPL wickets 105 - Lasith Malinga 118 - Yuzvendra Chahal 124 - Jasprit Bumrah* 137 - Dwayne Bravo 139 - Bhuvneswar Kumar
91 off 30 with one over left for Bumrah. If these two remain at the crease they will fancy knocking down 40-45 off the last two overs
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Appeal for LBW. not given and we will not even need HawkEye because impact is well outside off stump

Gerald Coetzee to Tristan Stubbs, leg byes, 1 run, round the wicket angle and then the off-side yorker, Stubbs got foxed a bit by that line as he was shaping up for a scoop, ball missed the bat, hit the boot and rolled to the leg-side. Impact way outside off stump of course

Gerald Coetzee to Pant, 1 run, ugly scoop or whatever that Pant was trying to do with that leg-side yorker that went as a low full toss. No feet, just tried to lean and scoop it behind square, ball flies towards deep square leg

Gerald Coetzee to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, this is some shot! If low full tosses aren't tough to hit already, Gerald Coetzee took pace off and Stubbs managed to nail the slog sweep, not exactly middled but clears deep mid-wicket
Gerald Coetzee to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, fast yorker, Stubbs digs it out to deep mid-wicket
Gerald Coetzee to Pant, no run, again cement-feeted digging of the ball from Pant. Gerald Coetzee stretches his left hand out but it doesn't stick
Gerald Coetzee to Pant, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Pant, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! And he throws it away too. Some of the ugliest three shots he's played in his career. If he didn't move his feet to hit attempted yorkers before, now almost yorks himself by moving and when he's in no position still tries to scoop or manufacture a shot. Only ends up slicing it high to the right of Hardik at extra-cover and that should be the game for MI because Stubbs can't do this alone. Pant c Hardik Pandya b Gerald Coetzee 1(3)
Axar Patel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Akash Madhwal [3.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack

Akash Madhwal to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, meanwhile Stubbs is putting on a masterclass of finishing! Akash Madhwal stays round the wicket for an off-side yorker, Stubbs sets base for a scoop and gets it over short third man

Akash Madhwal to Tristan Stubbs, no ball, SIX, oh the buzzer if off! But what an outstanding hit this is. Low full toss, only Stubbs knows how he's managed to get under this and smack it over square leg
Akash Madhwal to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, free-hit is an attempted off-side yorker from over the wicket, but it's a low full toss and Stubbs drives wide of mid-off. Already 15 off the first 2 balls
Akash Madhwal to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, lovely yorker, Stubbs digs it out to backward point
Akash Madhwal to Axar, no run, full and outside off stump, Axar drives to deep cover
Akash Madhwal to Axar, 1 run, excellent yorker, dug out to short fine leg
Three really good balls after a poor start from Akash Madhwal
Akash Madhwal to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, low full toss and it's swung away to the right of deep mid-wicket and it's a brilliant 19-ball fifty. He was with MI before. Now can he do it against MI?
Jasprit Bumrah [3.0-0-14-2] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Axar, no run, yorker on the off stump, Axar digs it out back to the bowler
Bumrah to Axar, 1 run, follows Axar as he backs away, yorker squeezed out to short third man
Bumrah to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, low full toss, only a hit along the ground to long-off
Bumrah to Axar, FOUR, backs away and manages to drive this low full toss past the dive at extra-cover. Took a step out to take it on the full
Bumrah to Axar, 1 run, another gun yorker, Axar puts bat on ball to backward point
Bumrah to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, low full toss, Stubbs drives to long-on
DC will be happy they haven't given a wicket away. Bumrah's gone for just 22 off 4 overs in this run fest. With the way Stubbs is hitting, if he can manage four big hits this over you never know
Romario Shepherd [3.0-0-33-1] is back into the attack
Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, and he starts off with a muscular flat six over long-on. Is Stubbs going to give it back to Romario? This by no means is over

Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, this is surely not over! Romario not known for his accurate yorkers like Bumrah, so he tries again and dishes out a slot ball. This is high over long-on and they have got 2 off two. Is Romario brave enough to take pace off?
Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, yes he is! Slow into the wicket outside off stump, Stubbs cuts to deep point and is off strike
Looks like Axar is runout. Yes!
Shepherd to Axar, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Shepherd to Axar, out Axar Run Out!! 1 run completed. Oh Axar! He wasn't aware of the threat at his end. Looked like an easy two with the ball going wide of long-on. Was a slower delivery that was dragged. Axar thought the ball was going to the bowler's end and how well did Ishan Kishan disguise Axar there. Didn't give away that the ball was coming towards him and last second rushed his hands to collect and ignite the stumps. Axar run out (Nabi/Ishan Kishan) 8(7) [4s-1]
Lalit Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shepherd to Lalit Yadav, 1 run, wide of off stump, Lalit digs it out square of the wicket

Shepherd to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, oh he tries the short delivery with fine leg in, thank you very much he says and smacks the pull over fine leg. 21 off that over. Had Stubbs got one more over the fence, this match would have been still on. What an innings he has played
Gerald Coetzee [3.0-0-30-1] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Lalit Yadav, 2 runs, low full toss, Lalit mistimes it to mid-wicket, oh Stubbs is okay to take the second run
Gerald Coetzee to Lalit Yadav, no run, yorker dug out back to the bowler and it's another dot
Gerald Coetzee to Lalit Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Lalit Yadav, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! That is a top catch by Ishan Kishan. Short delivery from Gerald Coetzee, Lalit Yadav looks to pull, gets a thick top edge. Ishan had to run all the way towards short fine leg and dive to complete that catch. Lalit Yadav c Ishan Kishan b Gerald Coetzee 3(4)
Kumar Kushagra, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Kushagra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Kushagra, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Sliced high and Gerald Coetzee has a third. Full delivery in the slot, Kushagra tries to hit the lofted drive straight and slices it high for Tilak to complete a good catch at point. Gerald Coetzee on a hat-trick! Kushagra c Tilak Varma b Gerald Coetzee 0(1)
Jhye Richardson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to J Richardson, 2 runs, yorker, Richardson digs it out to mid-wicket
Gerald Coetzee to J Richardson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to J Richardson, out Caught by Rohit!! It's a cue-ender and it's gone to Rohit at point. Short into the wicket, Richardson slogs and toe-ends it for an easy catch. The Mumbai Indians are finally smiling and off the blocks. J Richardson c Rohit b Gerald Coetzee 2(2)

19:15 Local Time, 13:45 GMT, 19:15 IST: Romario, the man who made the difference. That 32-run assault on Nortje turns out to be the gamechanger. But Stubbs made a valiant attempt all the way to the end with no support from his mates since his arrival at the crease. 235 was always tough even if was at the Wankhede but DC didn't bat well. Warner had a soft dismissal. Abhishek who came at No. 3 played shots but couldn't go at a brisk pace. Shaw played a good hand with a fifty. Stubbs was sent ahead of Pant and he was outstanding today, hitting even tough balls over the ropes. Bumrah was a massive influence for MI. If not for his yorkers and cunning off-speed deliveries, DC could have got a lot closer or even crossed the line because the rest were being taken for runs. Pant couldn't put bat on ball properly and Stubbs was left too much to do. In the end, Hardik and his team finally got their smiles back and they do a lap of honour to the kids who have turned up today. Stay tuned for the post-match presentation...

Rishabh Pant | DC captain - Definitely we were in contention, but we didn't have enough runs in the batting powerplay, especially when you're chasing such a big score., We batted well in the next few overs, but it's not easy to constantly score 15 rpo for many overs. Yes, we had a few bad overs (with the ball), but it does happen at times. The bowlers needed to bowl into the wicket, slower ones and the variations were important. The bowlers needed to understand the conditions well. I think we need to improve on a few areas - death-over bowling and our batting as well.

Ishan Kishan - I think we played according to our potential, this is the sort of cricket we are known to play for. It wasn't easy after the batting powerplay, the fielders go back and we decided that the batting powerplay was the right time to attack the bowlers. He has been working hard (on Romario Shepherd), wasn't playing, but always gave 100% at the nets. We were looking towards that one over, we know he's very powerful and has the ability to clear boundaries. We've been talking with the coaches on all departments (of the game), as a keeper, it's important to get the field placings right. It's difficult for the captain, he can't look at the angles, that's where I can chip in as a wicket-keeper.

Hardik Pandya | MI captain - It was a lot of hard work. We had to clear our minds and make sure that we believed. We will be making tactical changes here and there but this will be our 12 and settling our team now is important. There's a lot of love and care going around in the changeroom. Belief and backing each other is the attitude out there. Everyone believed we need just one win. It was an amazing start today, always wonderful to get 70 odd in 6 overs.
